\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 No, I don\rquote t know, because we never talked about her age. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16346414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 Merthyr.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16346414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 Did she have any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 She came to Whitchurch - now I can tell you the story, she - she used to love to tell the story she did. She came t
o Whitchurch - to the house opposite to us, you know the big house opposite to us? Well people - from Merthyr who was a schoolmaster in Tredodyn and my grandmother was the caretaker of the same school. And she came to Whitchurch - to Merthyr one - time, a
nd she said to my - my granny, you wouldn\rquote t let Polly come to Whitchurch to me would you she said? They couldn\rquote t get maids you see. Well I don\rquote t know, she said, I\rquote ll ask her. And oh my mother jumped at it. And that\rquote 
s how she came to Whitchurch, to that house opposite us. And dada - was lodging in - where we are living now. And that\rquote s how they met one another. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16346414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 Did she work at all after she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 Oh yes, she used to go out - they used to come after her you see. I\rquote ll tell you what happen
ed you see - my mother knew the Kittles, the builders - of those - most of the houses on Church Road. And - he used to come, and he knew my father, personally like you know, and he used to come down to the shop, and - he asked my mother one day if she kne
w of anybody that would come and - clean the new houses out ready for the - whenever they came in. Well she didn\rquote t know anybody then at the moment. But if you\rquote 
re stuck, she said, my mother - could turn around and do anything you see. But she done too much mind. She said, I\rquote ll help you out - but no, I\rquote m telling stories, I\rquote 
m behind my story now. Now he came to ours to ask my mother if she could go down and give his mother - a hand, see. And she used to go down once a week. I don\rquote t know what she used to do ther
e. Once a week she used to go down to his house, he lived down here somewhere, I don\rquote t know where. That\rquote s how they got familiar, and then he wanted somebody to scrub a house on Church Road, well my mother couldn\rquote 
t do that herself, but we happened to know somebody that would do it. And this person wouldn\rquote t go there herself, my mother had to go with her. She was afraid of the men. You see. And - and that\rquote 
s how they got - more friendly with the Kittles, you see, and oh he used to come on there whenever he wanted a little job done, you know - do one house out, and then my mother - she couldn\rquote 
t do it herself, she had to find somebody else to do it you see. But she was the boss, if you can understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16346414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 She was organising it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 Yes, that\rquote s right, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16346414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 And he\rquote d go to watch them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 And she - yes, oh yes, she\rquote d go there. Yes, and then she got hold of this one particular per - person in Whitchurch, she\rquote 
s still in Whitchurch, and - she - no, she died didn\rquote t she, yes, not long ago - so I heard, and - but many wouldn\rquote 
t go without my mother. My mother had to go down, she was afraid of the men. You know. My mother used to go down with her - and take her - her dinner and she\rquote d be getting the dinner for them you know and - all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16346414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 While they did the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 But she was helping, mind, but she should never have done. She - she used to get the pay and she\rquote d pay - the other one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16346414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 Would she do that often, it wouldn\rquote t be full time work would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 Oh no, no, no, no. Oh no. While they were building the houses you see, and Church Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16346414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 What about the work in the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 
Oh well we were always in that lake. My mother and father, and then when I came old enough and my sister came old enough, we all used to help like you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16346414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 Would anybody look after you children while your mother was out working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 Oh well, no, we weren\rquote t very small when she started you see, oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16346414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 What about life at home when you were a child before you left school, the house you\rquote re living in now of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16346414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 How many rooms were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 
Three - three bedrooms, which are all in front. Was there. Then - you came down the stairs and you came down to the back kitchen. Then you went through a passage and - living room was one side and the shop the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16346414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 Did anyone else live in the house besides your mother and your father and your sister and you,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4927998 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1514656\charrsid14953505 No.
